<subSubSection id="C93BE8C68CAEB7DB6D3CA1F69C328193" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph id="399BF8073DBFEA60170F5674DA8E66E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E805AA34AAE6CBE3EB942E87274CE565" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
Herb perennial and stemless, rhizomatous. Leaves basal; petiole 4-8 cm, densely brown villous; leaf blade ovate, thickly chartaceous, 4.0-5.2 
<normalizedToken id="1486B20F24A66AAC39879D33C5841878" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.0-3.5 cm, adaxially setulose and rugose, abaxially glabrous amongst veins, sparsely brown villous along veins, base cordate, apex acute, margin biserrate, lateral veins 5-6 on each side of midrib, indistinct adaxially and distinct abaxially. Inflorescences axillary; peduncle 9-13 cm, densely brown villous; bracts 2, leaf-like, broadly ovate, 7-10 
<normalizedToken id="3340B3D9D2951872886AD84964BA6B20" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
ca. 5 mm, adaxially glabrous and abaxially villous, margin serrate. Pedicel 1-2.5 cm, villous. Calyx ca. 6 mm, 5-sect from 1/3; segments equal, triangular, ca. 4 
<normalizedToken id="C13BE6752E44970EF64FE12E7FA59156" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2 mm, margin entire below top, top crenate, adaxially glabrous, abaxially pubescent. Corolla yellow, 1.6-2.9 cm, outside strigose and inside glabrous; tube campanulate-cylindric, gradually slightly widening from middle of tube, 1.3-2 cm, 0.3-0.4 cm in diam., throat not constricted; limb 2-lipped; adaxial lip smaller, 3-5 mm, emarginate; abaxial lip larger, 3-lobed, lobes oblong, apex rounded, central lobe ovate, ca. 7 
<normalizedToken id="91537A2CF2E7ACA49B8AD82AA20469CC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5 mm, lateral lobes rotund, ca. 5 
<normalizedToken id="E4A0A9DA3F3336721A2F511AFBE2070A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5 mm. Stamens 4, coherent in 2 pairs, included, adaxial stamens 3-6 mm, adnate to corolla tube 7-13 mm from base, abaxial stamens 3-4 mm, adnate to corolla tube 13-16 mm from base; filaments tender, glabrous; anthers basifixed, oblong, 2-loculed, dehiscing longitudinally; staminode ca. 0.5 mm, adnate to corolla tube ca. 8 mm. Disc ring-like, 1-2 mm, 5-lobed shallowly. Pistil 0.9-1.8 cm, pubescent; ovary oblong, pubescent, 0.5-1.2 cm, 1-loculed; style glabrous, 0.4-0.6 cm; stigma 1, 2-lobed. Capsule straight, narrowly oblong, 3.4-4 cm 
<normalizedToken id="6C57F82542CDC42F8FCAC08A088DA77F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-0.9 cm, existing style ca. 0.7 cm. Seeds not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3EDED3F492383C37ECAC9A5812EB787B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="35F1C15D5A4EF39227C9A7FF08F911F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Distribution, habitat and phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B026431A1A33C8A10222D54999C0E56" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">The new species is endemic to SE Yunnan of China, on rocks or limestone cliffs. Flowering is July-September; and fruiting is October-January the following year.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F7D25F8E71F50381D4B13122D3A29798" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="DECDCE2697A4EF26ED5BE865DE347A86" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8DF0696ACD7D40EF64E0B997F5AEF24F" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
So far, there are two populations of the new species observed in the field (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="45A36926656B6FCCB77D3D462B471501" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. The localities of the four new species and the other species of Oreocharis s. l. from SW Yunnan and SE Yunnan in SW China. The districts are shown in Yunnan province, SW China." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys..32284.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/445708" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">1</figureCitation>
). One is in the type locality at the core position of the nature reserve with ca. 500 mature individuals and ca. 10, 000 m2 (100 m 
<normalizedToken id="30159202037B8545380AD397E4FA34F6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
100 m) area, the other is the Pingbian county with ca. 120 mature individuals and ca. 1, 200 m2 (20 m 
<normalizedToken id="A02714DAA2789EC3BDEA3CA2B10AA6F9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
60 m) area. According to the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, the new species is hereby assessed as &quot;Vulnerable (VU)&quot; (D1+D2). (
<bibRefCitation id="E7850C88D6EACA5C785B2062CB6F5B10" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore)" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/technical-documents/categories-and-criteria" refId="B6" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN red list categories and criteria, Version 3.1. 2nd edn. IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland &amp; Cambridge. Available from: http://www.iucnredlist.org/technical-documents/categories-and-criteria" title="IUCN red list categories and criteria, Version 3.1. 2 nd edn. IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland &amp; Cambridge. Available from:" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/technical-documents/categories-and-criteria" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
