<subSubSection id="BA019BD04AE422C2C03C0C6A74A6DA9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D50F2A79D5F4D3E9A58DDAA35714820B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA4417A6F714EDDD10654F4D514D9F9D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The species is named after the pubescent fruits (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0765FB886B77837DF4308B58E30BB314" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Oreocharis eriocarpa W. H. Chen &amp; Y. M. Shui, sp. nov. (A-F) A habit B leaf adaxial surface C leaf abaxial surface D bracts E ovary and disc F dense pubescent ovary and disc; O. wenshanensis (G-K) G habitat H plant I leaf adaxial surface J leaf abaxial surface K flower. Photography by He De-Ming (A-E, K), Zhang Ting (E), Chen Li (F), Shui Yu-Min (G, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys..32284.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/445709" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">2F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CE49C6097AC8E93367E4F668AAE797FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="notes">
<paragraph id="260F4C50685D9493CB85C6A3558B78DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="76657748F950D42148A43BD734CF1839" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The new species is endemic to the border regions of Honghe Hani and Yi Autonomous Prefecture and Wenshan Zhuang and Miao Autonomous Prefecture in SE Yunnan (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3327D939C483A3F9A6215BBD32E21430" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. The localities of the four new species and the other species of Oreocharis s. l. from SW Yunnan and SE Yunnan in SW China. The districts are shown in Yunnan province, SW China." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys..32284.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/445708" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">1</figureCitation>
), at ca. 2100 m elevation. It is unique in its pubescent ovary and fruits (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="04DD59D5D1F00F4451F13A4F69FE69DD" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Oreocharis eriocarpa W. H. Chen &amp; Y. M. Shui, sp. nov. (A-F) A habit B leaf adaxial surface C leaf abaxial surface D bracts E ovary and disc F dense pubescent ovary and disc; O. wenshanensis (G-K) G habitat H plant I leaf adaxial surface J leaf abaxial surface K flower. Photography by He De-Ming (A-E, K), Zhang Ting (E), Chen Li (F), Shui Yu-Min (G, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys..32284.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/445709" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">2A-F</figureCitation>
). Its similar species (
<taxonomicName id="89CF64313C4FE6A1E51AE05834100EB3" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Oreocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oreocharis concava" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava">
<emphasis id="A8D37949A6CBE19275AC7E708550C3C9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Oreocharis concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is distributed in Northwest Yunnan at 2,800-3,600 m elevation, viz. Dali Bai Autonomous Prefecture, Lijiang District and Deqin Zang Autonomous Prefecture (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AEACC96F87CBF3D276A4F13F50270E20" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. The localities of the four new species and the other species of Oreocharis s. l. from SW Yunnan and SE Yunnan in SW China. The districts are shown in Yunnan province, SW China." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys..32284.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/445708" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">1</figureCitation>
). Table 
<tableCitation id="EB5FDF1F4EE8A0405EA5ADFD7FEA0D4E" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Differences in characters between Oreocharis eriocarpa and O. concava in Gesneriaceae." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/9837B4163004A8C3C19532C74E8E38B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="9837B4163004A8C3C19532C74E8E38B3">1</tableCitation>
shows the other differences between the above two species. Thus, there is an obvious geographical substitution between the above two species. Besides, after the examination of type specimens in PE and consulting the literature (
<bibRefCitation id="90F6129F1B7D833C6FECEBF112A66F10" author="Pan, KY" journalOrPublisher="Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="264 - 293" refId="B12" refString="Pan, KY, 1987. Taxonomy of the genus Oreocharis (Gesneriaceae). Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 25: 264 - 293" title="Taxonomy of the genus Oreocharis (Gesneriaceae)." volume="25" year="1987">Pan 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DABF7472CF24034D74A2CB31BFC783A6" author="Li, ZY" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 5. Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B9" refString="Li, ZY, Wang, YZ, 2005. Plants of Gesneriaceae in China. Henan Science Technology Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 14-47." title="Plants of Gesneriaceae in China. Henan Science Technology Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 14 - 47." year="2005">Li and Wang 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9500C82C57019CA6EDAAFE9E00D670BA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.23.1.1" author="Moeller, M" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 36" refId="B11" refString="Moeller, M, Middleton, D, Nishii, K, Wei, YG, Sontag, S, Weber, A, 2011. A new delineation for Oreocharis incorporating an additional ten genera of Chinese Gesneriaceae. Phytotaxa 23 (1): 1 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.23.1.1" title="A new delineation for Oreocharis incorporating an additional ten genera of Chinese Gesneriaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.23.1.1" volume="23" year="2011">
<normalizedToken id="CCFAF4F16F122256E523370D8BB20B57" originalValue="Möller">Moeller</normalizedToken>
et al. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
), the new species seems similar to its another variety [
<taxonomicName id="5CF0282B9763B0A88FA903B325E1FBD7" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Oreocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oreocharis concava subsp. var. var. angustifolia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="concava" subSpecies="var." variety="angustifolia">Oreocharis concava var. angustifolia</taxonomicName>
(K.Y.Pan) Mich.
<normalizedToken id="A7AD42E23A227E6BB8F2E68023A2DC29" originalValue="Möller">Moeller</normalizedToken>
&amp; A.Weber] in the pubescent ovary, but obviously different from it in its ovate blade (
<emphasis id="A9FAF8DAF78E7DE946778CFB8C2DFC0E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">vs.</emphasis>
elliptic). It is possible that the latter variety might be a different species from the original variety and needs to be explored in the future.
</paragraph>
